NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There was a question about whether West should open. Even if you use Bergen "adjusted HCP" it still meets the rule of 20. 12 HCP, less one for the @CQx which gives her 11 "adjusted HCP" + 9 cards in the red suits which still equals 20. Remember, use the rule of 20, not just HCP (adjusted or not) to determine whether or not to open.|
PG| ***** 96 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I believe in the rule of 20. You can either use the simple rule of 20, in which case your hand is definitely an opener (12 HCP + 9 cards in the reds = 21). Or if you want to use the Bergen adjusted HCP method, you deduct for dubious doubletons, add for quality suits, and add or subtract for quacks vs. ace/tens.|
PG| ***** 97 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|You never count length when deciding whether you meet the rule of 20 because the length part of the rule takes care of long suits. Basically, the only time you pass a 12 point hand is if it is 4-3-3-3 because then it only equals 19 (12 + 7) by the rule of 20.|
