at|^B@2
I found mixing responses to Jacoby 2N and Frank Sinatra was interesting so we decided to do a BBO movie on it. However, we run into problem when Mel, in his attempt to reach slam with Rule of Frank Sinatra after Jacoby 2N, used control bidding style which is different than what Howard uses and like to teach.|
PG| ***** 138 ***** |


AT|

Apparently, Mel recommends control bidding only with aces. However, many experts these days play "Italian Style" control bids where a control bid shows a first or second round control (ace, king, singleton, or void). Howard strongly feel that "Italian Style" is vastly superior. That is what he teaches. Nevertheless, although he is very flexible and open-minded about the different styles practiced by different experts, in control bidding it was "All Or Nothing At All." |
PG| ***** 139 ***** |


AT|

So, making sure Rule of Frank Sinatra unmolested, we modified Mel's control bidding when required based on what Howard teaches with the final contracts unchanged. I hope Mel understands. We have to put some bread on the table you know -:). Please refer to this |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/hondoviewer/hondoviewer.php?sf=slamlesson3^*N|CP||AT| link for Howard's lesson "Italian Style" control bidding.|
PG| ***** 140 ***** |


