NT|^B@2
So you should bid 3@H. This shows slam interest (if you had no slam interest you would bid 4@H) and asks partner to begin bidding controls. Because you have  2 small spades, you want to make sure you do not have 2 quick spade losers. So if partner bypasses the 3@S control bid, you know you have 2 quick spade losers and will stop in 4@H.|MB|3hp|
